## Quick Start

```python
from backend.depth_sensing import create_tof_sensor, ToFConfig

config = ToFConfig(
    sensor_id="{{ sensors[0].sensor_id }}",
    resolution=({{ sensors[0].width }}, {{ sensors[0].height }}),
    fps={{ sensors[0].default_fps }},
    modulation_freq_mhz={{ sensors[0].modulation_freq_mhz }},
)
sensor = create_tof_sensor("{{ sensors[0].sensor_id }}", config)
sensor.connect()
depth_frame = sensor.capture()
print(f"Depth frame shape: {depth_frame.shape}, dtype: {depth_frame.dtype}")
sensor.disconnect()
```

## Stereo Pipeline

The stereo pipeline accepts a rectified image pair and produces a dense disparity
map using Semi-Global Block Matching (SGBM) or classical Block Matching (BM).

```python
from backend.depth_sensing import StereoPipeline, StereoConfig

stereo_cfg = StereoConfig(
    algorithm="sgbm",
    num_disparities={{ stereo.num_disparities }},
    block_size={{ stereo.block_size }},
    p1={{ stereo.p1 }},
    p2={{ stereo.p2 }},
)
pipeline = StereoPipeline(stereo_cfg)
rectified_left, rectified_right = pipeline.rectify(left_img, right_img, calib)
disparity = pipeline.compute_disparity(rectified_left, rectified_right)
```

## Point Cloud Processing

Depth maps or disparity maps can be projected into 3D point clouds. Both PCL
(via pclpy) and Open3D back-ends are supported.

```python
from backend.depth_sensing import PointCloudEngine

engine = PointCloudEngine(backend="{{ point_cloud.default_backend }}")
cloud = engine.from_depth_map(depth_frame, intrinsics)
cloud = engine.statistical_outlier_removal(cloud, nb_neighbors=20, std_ratio=2.0)
engine.save(cloud, "output.ply")
```

